  "translations": {
    "en": "A son of Uthman ibn Maz'un (may Allah be pleased with him) passed away, and his grief intensified to the point where he took a place in his house as a place of worship to devote himself in prayer therein. This reached the Messenger of Allah (may Allah bless him and his family), and he said to him: O Uthman, indeed Allah, Blessed and Exalted, has not prescribed monasticism for us. The monasticism of my nation is striving in the way of Allah.",
